<paragraph pageId="180" pageNumber="181">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cephaloleia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cephaloleia fryella" order="Coleoptera" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fryella">Cephaloleia fryella</taxonomicName>
and can be distinguished by the vertex of the head having a medial carina and by the sinuate lateral margins of the pronotum.
</paragraph>
